page.title: 08Ecology 3: Birds
page.content:
Birds of prey commonly resident and breeding in the area are the buzzard, kestrel and sparrowhawk. Others include wood pigeon, stock dove, collared dove, song thrush, mistle thrush, blackbird, robin, yellow- hammer, bullfinch, goldfinch, green- finch, blue, great, coal and long tailed tit, grey and pied wagtail, skylark, hedgesparrow, wren, dipper, tree-creeper, willow warbler, magpie, rook, carrion crow, jackdaw, partridge and tawny owl. Resident but not breeding is the grey heron; the raven and peregrine falcon have bred within recent years and are still regularly sighted.
Winter visitors include brambling, field fare, redwing and greylag goose.
